    Welcome to the Intelligent Transportation Systems - U.S Department of
                               Transportation
   Notices

     * FHWA issues a Notice for preliminary applications from
       public/public or public/private partnerships for participation in
       the fiscal year 2003 ITS integration program, with a focus on
       enhancing the security of the surface transportation systems.
       Applications are requested by April 1, 2002.
     * ITS America has completed development of the Ten-Year ITS Program
       Plan, which is available on their website.
     * DOT seeks public agency applications for "511 Model Deployment" by
       March 18.
     * Job Notice: ITS Public Safety Program Coordinator, closing date
       01/25/02. For more information contact E.English at (202) 366.0541
     * FHWA Recognizes Outstanding Traveler Information Websites.
     * FHWA Announces Intelligent Transportation Systems Tests to
       Facilitate Freight Movement
     * 511 - America's Traveler Information Number. 511 Deployment
       Coalition Publishes "Implementation Guidelines for Launching 511
       Services." PDF 1.14MB
     * DOT Announces Test to Prevent Run-off-the-Road Crashes
     * The Truth About the Costs of ITS: Implications for Improving
       Planning and Operations in Traffic Management. Click here
     * Announcements: DOT grant for driver performance study awarded.
       Click here
     * FHWA announces 511 Planning Assistance Program - On July 23, the
       FHWA published a notice in the Federal register announcing the
       availability of up to $100,000 in Federal funds to help States
       organize and plan to implement 511 Traveler Information services.
       The intent is to develop statewide plans around which 511 can be
       deployed in metropolitan area, intercity corridors, and statewide,
       as appropriate. Applications must be received before June 2001.
       This program replaces the former 511 conversion program.

